Wapiti
Web application vulnerability scanner

Web Application
Description
Wapiti allows you to audit the security of your websites or web applications. It performs black-box scanning by crawling pages and injecting payloads.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which wapiti
Install command:

sudo apt install wapiti
Basic Syntax
wapiti -u <URL>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
wapiti -u http://target.com

Full scan	Complete web app audit	
wapiti -u http://target.com -m sql

SQL injection only	Test SQLi specifically	
wapiti -u http://target.com -m xss

XSS testing	Test for XSS	
wapiti -u http://target.com -o report

Generate report	Save findings	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Start with target URL
2
Let wapiti crawl the site
3
Review discovered forms/parameters
4
Wait for injection tests
5
Review generated report
Understanding the Output
Shows discovered vulnerabilities by category. Report includes affected URLs and payloads.

Important Warnings
•
Active injection testing
•
Can cause application errors
•
May trigger WAF alerts
•
Use only on authorized apps
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
